8. Selector must be specific enough to uniquely identify the element
9. Consider the action type when choosing selector (click vs type vs hover)
10. For submit/login buttons: Check both <button> and <input type="submit"> elements, match by:
    - id attribute (e.g., #Login)
    - name attribute (e.g., input[name="Login"])
    - value attribute text (e.g., input[value*="Log In"])
    - type="submit" combined with context (e.g., input[type="submit"] within a form)

CONFIDENCE SCORING:
- 0.9-1.0: Exact match with unique identifier (id, data-testid)
- 0.7-0.9: Good match with specific class or attribute
- 0.5-0.7: Partial match, may need refinement
- <0.5: Uncertain match, not recommended

